Using rules of DataTypes

From Elastos Developer Website
Jump to: navigation, search

A notable feature of CAR data type is its self-descriptive.


How to use in CAR files
In CAR files, developers can use CAR data type in accordance with the rules of CAR grammar but can not use C++ or other data types. CAR data type mainly used to define the types of the interface method parameters.

Please note that, car file does not support the form of underlined data types, such as BufferOf_<>, StringBuf_<> etc.


How to use in C++ files
In CAR files, developers can use both CAR data types and C++ data types as long as them meeting the standard use of C++ syntax.

Please note also both in CAR files and in C++ files, developers must use the Elastos namespace.

The talbe below shows the the rules about CAR Data Types as parameters of interface functions using in car files.

5) [in] ArrayOf<Type> *
